title: I-35E North Photo Archive
text: These photos show I-35E North Stemmons Freeway before completion of expansion projects.

imageStatus.note: The freeway will be widened at this location as part of the $655 million expansion project which began in 2022.

images.caption: Looking southbound at Luna Road. North of I-635, I-35E has 6 main lanes and 2 HOV lanes. Frontage roads are continuous.

imageStatus.note: Two reversible managed lanes were built in the center area of the freeway, opening in 2017. In 2022 work started on the the second and final phase, which will widen the freeway to 8 main lanes (4 each  way).

images.caption: Looking southbound at Frankford with a zoomed-in view, showing the Bush Turnpike interchange in the distance.

imageStatus.note: The addition of collector-distributor lanes was completed in 2017
The addition of collector-distributor lanes was completed in 2017
In 2017 phase 1 of the expansion program was completed, which reconfigured the main lanes in this area and completed the north half of the interchange.
